{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The speech-to-text output preserves speaker labels so that the summary can attribute statements to specific attendees.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Failure boundary is real diarization/model output, not local parsing. A mocked STT response would hide label-loss failures. Adversarial critique: this could be System if only transport/HTTP errors mattered, but behavior text is about label preservation quality. Top-2 contrast: Agentic beats System because correctness depends on what STT predicts; it would flip to System if the behavior were only 'handles STT API timeout/retry'. Rejection gate: Workflow rejected because behavior text targets a single model output property (STT labels), not multi-agentic sequencing.","test_description":"Run a real recorded multi-speaker clip through the real STT path and assert returned transcript contains correct speaker-labeled utterances used downstream for attribution.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.18}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Transcript parsing extracts explicit task assignments (assignee + task text) into the summary input structure.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Behavior is deterministic parsing/structuring logic at one local boundary; no required external infra or model judgment. Adversarial critique: could be Integration if parser-service/schema handoff is where bugs occur, but behavior text does not require cross-module state propagation. Top-2 contrast: Unit beats Integration because a direct parser function test can expose extraction failures; it would flip to Integration if extraction only happens after service-layer orchestration across modules.","test_description":"Feed representative transcript lines into the parsing function/object and assert exact assignee/task fields in the produced summary-input structure.","plan_consistent":