del outputs across steps. Top-2 contrast: Workflow beats Agentic because correctness spans chained model calls over segments; it would flip to Agentic if only one segment/model call were involved.","test_description":"Run a >60-minute real meeting audio through full segmentation, sequential processing, and merge path with real model calls; assert final output is one structured summary with consistent cross-segment decisions/action items.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.09,"Agentic":0.22,"Workflow":0.63}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"The full pipeline (upload audio, transcribe, summarize, deliver structured output) completes without manual intervention for a real meeting recording.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Explicit end-to-end real run with multiple external/model stages; failures emerge from chained infra+agentic interactions. Any isolated or mocked layer can mask real orchestration failures. Adversarial critique: could be System if model quality were irrelevant, but pipeline includes real transcribe+summarize stages whose outputs drive next steps. Top-2 contrast: Workflow beats System because multiple agentic decisions are sequenced; it would flip to System if the test only verified transport/job completion with fixed deterministic model stubs.","test_description":"Execute production-like pipeline on a real meeting recording from upload through delivery and assert successful completion plus valid structured payload (`action_items`, `decisions`, attendee attributions) without operator intervention.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.01,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.78}}]}
